# 🎨 Color Detection from Images

A simple and interactive web application that lets users upload an image and click on any part of it to detect the color at that point. The app displays the RGB values and the closest known color name from a predefined dataset.

## 🚀 Features

- Upload and view any image
- Click anywhere on the image to detect the pixel color
- View the color name and its RGB values in real-time
- Display a reference color box filled with the detected color
- Clean and user-friendly UI built with Streamlit

## 📸 Use Case

This app is useful for:
- Designers choosing consistent brand colors
- Developers working on accessibility
- Artists analyzing color palettes from artwork

## 🛠️ Technologies Used

- Python
- OpenCV (`cv2`)
- Pandas
- Streamlit

